# Required ancestor SHA for the commit queue.
#
# This file is read from origin/main at CI time, so changes here
# take effect immediately for all new queue pushes — even if the
# pusher hasn't fetched.
#
# Any branch pushed to the commit queue must include this SHA as
# an ancestor. This proves the submitter has rebased onto the fix
# after an industrial accident.
#
# How to update after an incident:
#   1. Fix the problem on main.
#   2. Replace the SHA below with the fix commit.
#   3. Push to main.
#
# Set to an empty file (no SHA line) to disable the check.
